OL,6,F2002 The BBC confirms that Michael
OL,7,FBuerk will leave the Ten o'Clock News
OL,8,Fby the end of the year. Michael Buerk
OL,9,Fconfirmed his plans the previous
OL,10,Fevening, saying:J"By November I will
OL,11,Fhave presented the main evening news
OL,12,Fmore than 4,000 times. It's more than
OL,13,Fenough."JThe official BBC statement
OL,14,Fsaid that he would continue to work as
OL,15,Fa presenter on BBC Radio 4 and on news/
OL,16,Fcurrent affairs specials. It also
OL,17,Fmentioned possible foreign
OL,18,Fassignments, including "babysitting"
OL,19,Fsome of the BBC's foreign bureaux -
OL,20,Fwith a spell in India apparently
OL,21,Falready lined up.
